@startuml
title Application Lifecycle - Beginner Flow

skinparam ParticipantPadding 8

actor "User code" as User
participant "Application" as App
participant "Window" as Window
participant "Widgets" as Widgets

User -> App : create windows
User -> App : run()

loop until quit or no windows remain
	App -> Window : poll platform events
	App -> Widgets : update
	App -> Widgets : collect drawing
	App -> Window : render frame
end

alt user closes a window
	Window -> Widgets : close requested event
	alt event consumed
		Widgets --> Window : keep open
	else not consumed
		Window -> Window : close and release resources
	end
end

User -> App : quit(exitCode)
App --> User : run() returns exitCode

note over User,Widgets
Beginner rule of thumb: build windows before run(),
customize widgets, and call quit() when your program
should stop from user code or host integration.
end note

@enduml
